3/*++
4/* NAME
5/* milter 3
6/* SUMMARY
7/* generic MTA-side mail filter interface
8/* SYNOPSIS
9/* #include <milter.h>
10/*
11/* MILTERS *milter_create(milter_names, conn_timeout, cmd_timeout,
12/* msg_timeout, protocol, def_action,
13/* conn_macros, helo_macros,
14/* mail_macros, rcpt_macros,
15/* data_macros, eoh_macros,
16/* eod_macros, unk_macros,
17/* macro_deflts)
18/* const char *milter_names;
19/* int conn_timeout;
20/* int cmd_timeout;
21/* int msg_timeout;
22/* const char *protocol;
23/* const char *def_action;
24/* const char *conn_macros;
25/* const char *helo_macros;
26/* const char *mail_macros;
27/* const char *rcpt_macrps;
28/* const char *data_macros;
29/* const char *eoh_macros;
30/* const char *eod_macros;
31/* const char *unk_macros;
32/* const char *macro_deflts;
33/*
34/* void milter_free(milters)
35/* MILTERS *milters;
36/*
37/* void milter_macro_callback(milters, mac_lookup, mac_context)
38/* const char *(*mac_lookup)(const char *name, void *context);
39/* void *mac_context;
40/*
41/* void milter_edit_callback(milters, add_header, upd_header,
42/* ins_header, del_header, chg_from,
43/* add_rcpt, add_rcpt_par, del_rcpt,
44/* repl_body, context)
45/* MILTERS *milters;
46/* MILTER_ADD_HEADER_FN add_header;
47/* MILTER_EDIT_HEADER_FN upd_header;
48/* MILTER_EDIT_HEADER_FN ins_header;
49/* MILTER_DEL_HEADER_FN del_header;
50/* MILTER_EDIT_FROM_FN chg_from;
51/* MILTER_EDIT_RCPT_FN add_rcpt;
52/* MILTER_EDIT_RCPT_PAR_FN add_rcpt_par;
53/* MILTER_EDIT_RCPT_FN del_rcpt;
54/* MILTER_EDIT_BODY_FN repl_body;
55/* void *context;
56/*
57/* const char *milter_conn_event(milters, client_name, client_addr,
58/* client_port, addr_family)
59/* MILTERS *milters;
60/* const char *client_name;
61/* const char *client_addr;
62/* const char *client_port;
63/* int addr_family;
64/*
65/* const char *milter_disc_event(milters)
66/* MILTERS *milters;
67/*
68/* const char *milter_helo_event(milters, helo_name, esmtp_flag)
69/* MILTERS *milters;
70/* const char *helo_name;
71/* int esmtp_flag;
72/*
73/* const char *milter_mail_event(milters, argv)
74/* MILTERS *milters;
75/* const char **argv;
76/*
77/* const char *milter_rcpt_event(milters, flags, argv)
78/* MILTERS *milters;
79/* int flags;
80/* const char **argv;
81/*
82/* const char *milter_data_event(milters)
83/* MILTERS *milters;
84/*
85/* const char *milter_unknown_event(milters, command)
86/* MILTERS *milters;
87/* const char *command;
88/*
89/* const char *milter_other_event(milters)
90/* MILTERS *milters;
91/*
92/* const char *milter_message(milters, qfile, data_offset, auto_hdrs)
93/* MILTERS *milters;
94/* VSTREAM *qfile;
95/* off_t data_offset;
96/* ARGV *auto_hdrs;
97/*
98/* const char *milter_abort(milters)
99/* MILTERS *milters;
100/*
101/* int milter_send(milters, fp)
102/* MILTERS *milters;
103/* VSTREAM *fp;
104/*
105/* MILTERS *milter_receive(fp, count)
106/* VSTREAM *fp;
107/* int count;
108/*
109/* int milter_dummy(milters, fp)
110/* MILTERS *milters;
111/* VSTREAM *fp;
112/* DESCRIPTION
113/* The functions in this module manage one or more milter (mail
114/* filter) clients. Currently, only the Sendmail 8 filter
115/* protocol is supported.
116/*
117/* The functions that inspect content or envelope commands
118/* return either an SMTP reply ([45]XX followed by enhanced
119/* status code and text), "D" (discard), "H" (quarantine),
120/* "S" (shutdown connection), or a null pointer, which means
121/* "no news is good news".
122/*
123/* milter_create() instantiates the milter clients specified
124/* with the milter_names argument. The conn_macros etc.
125/* arguments specify the names of macros that are sent to the
126/* mail filter applications upon a connect etc. event, and the
127/* macro_deflts argument specifies macro defaults that will be used
128/* only if the application's lookup call-back returns null. This
129/* function should be called during process initialization,
130/* before entering a chroot jail. The timeout parameters specify
131/* time limits for the completion of the specified request
132/* classes. The protocol parameter specifies a protocol version
133/* and optional extensions. When the milter application is
134/* unavailable, the milter client will go into a suitable error
135/* state as specified with the def_action parameter (i.e.
136/* reject, tempfail or accept all subsequent events).
137/*
138/* milter_free() disconnects from the milter instances that
139/* are still opened, and destroys the data structures created
140/* by milter_create(). This function is safe to call at any
141/* point after milter_create().
142/*
143/* milter_macro_callback() specifies a call-back function and
144/* context for macro lookup. This function must be called
145/* before milter_conn_event().
146/*
147/* milter_edit_callback() specifies call-back functions and
148/* context for editing the queue file after the end-of-data
149/* is received. This function must be called before milter_message();
150/*
151/* milter_conn_event() reports an SMTP client connection event
152/* to the specified milter instances, after sending the macros
153/* specified with the milter_create() conn_macros argument.
154/* This function must be called before reporting any other
155/* events.
156/*
157/* milter_disc_event() reports an SMTP client disconnection
158/* event to the specified milter instances. No events can
159/* reported after this call. To simplify usage, redundant calls
160/* of this function are NO-OPs and don't raise a run-time
161/* error.
162/*
163/* milter_helo_event() reports a HELO or EHLO event to the
164/* specified milter instances, after sending the macros that
165/* were specified with the milter_create() helo_macros argument.
166/*
167/* milter_mail_event() reports a MAIL FROM event to the specified
168/* milter instances, after sending the macros that were specified
169/* with the milter_create() mail_macros argument.
170/*
171/* milter_rcpt_event() reports an RCPT TO event to the specified
172/* milter instances, after sending the macros that were specified
173/* with the milter_create() rcpt_macros argument. The flags
174/* argument supports the following:
175/* .IP MILTER_FLAG_WANT_RCPT_REJ
176/* When this flag is cleared, invoke all milters. When this
177/* flag is set, invoke only milters that want to receive
178/* rejected recipients; with Sendmail V8 Milters, {rcpt_mailer}
179/* is set to "error", {rcpt_host} is set to an enhanced status
180/* code, and {rcpt_addr} is set to descriptive text.
181/* .PP
182/* milter_data_event() reports a DATA event to the specified
183/* milter instances, after sending the macros that were specified
184/* with the milter_create() data_macros argument.
185/*
186/* milter_unknown_event() reports an unknown command event to
187/* the specified milter instances, after sending the macros
188/* that were specified with the milter_create() unk_macros
189/* argument.
190/*
191/* milter_other_event() returns the current default mail filter
192/* reply for the current SMTP connection state; it does not
193/* change milter states. A null pointer result means that all
194/* is well. This function can be used for SMTP commands such
195/* as AUTH, STARTTLS that don't have their own milter event
196/* routine.
197/*
198/* milter_message() sends the message header and body to the
199/* to the specified milter instances, and sends the macros
200/* specified with the milter_create() eoh_macros after the
201/* message header, and with the eod_macros argument at
202/* the end. Each milter sees the result of any changes made
203/* by a preceding milter. This function must be called with
204/* as argument an open Postfix queue file.
205/*
206/* milter_abort() cancels a mail transaction in progress. To
207/* simplify usage, redundant calls of this function are NO-OPs
208/* and don't raise a run-time error.
209/*
210/* milter_send() sends a list of mail filters over the specified
211/* stream. When given a null list pointer, a "no filter"
212/* indication is sent. The result is non-zero in case of
213/* error.
214/*
215/* milter_receive() receives the specified number of mail
216/* filters over the specified stream. The result is a null
217/* pointer when no milters were sent, or when an error happened.
218/*
219/* milter_dummy() is like milter_send(), except that it sends
220/* a dummy, but entirely valid, mail filter list.
221/* SEE ALSO
222/* milter8(3) Sendmail 8 Milter protocol
223/* DIAGNOSTICS
224/* Panic: interface violation.
225/* Fatal errors: memory allocation problem.
226/* LICENSE
227/* .ad
228/* .fi
229/* The Secure Mailer license must be distributed with this software.
230/* AUTHOR(S)
231/* Wietse Venema
232/* IBM T.J. Watson Research
233/* P.O. Box 704
234/* Yorktown Heights, NY 10598, USA
235/*
236/* Wietse Venema
237/* Google, Inc.
238/* 111 8th Avenue
239/* New York, NY 10011, USA

274/* milter_macro_defaults_create - parse default macro entries */
275
276HTABLE *milter_macro_defaults_create(const char *macro_defaults)
277{
278 const char myname[] = "milter_macro_defaults_create";
279 char *saved_defaults = mystrdup(macro_defaults);
280 char *cp = saved_defaults;
281 HTABLE *table = 0;
282 VSTRING *canon_buf = 0;
283 char *nameval;
284
285 while ((nameval = mystrtokq(&cp, CHARS_COMMA_SP, CHARS_BRACE)) != 0) {
286 const char *err;
287 char *name;
288 char *value;
289
290 /*
291 * Split the input into (name, value) pairs. Allow the forms
292 * name=value and { name = value }, where the last form ignores
293 * whitespace after the opening "{", around the "=", and before the
294 * closing "}". A name may also be specified as {name}.
295 *
296 * Use the form {name} for table lookups, because that is the form of
297 * the S8_MAC_* macro names.
298 */
299 if (*nameval == CHARS_BRACE[0]
300 && nameval[balpar(nameval, CHARS_BRACE)] != '='
301 && (err = extpar(&nameval, CHARS_BRACE, EXTPAR_FLAG_NONE)) != 0)
302 msg_fatal("malformed default macro entry: %s in \"%s\"",
303 err, macro_defaults);
304 if ((err = split_nameval(nameval, &name, &value)) != 0)
305 msg_fatal("malformed default macro entry: %s in \"%s\"",
306 err, macro_defaults);
307 if (*name != '{') /* } */
308 name = STR(vstring_sprintf(canon_buf ? canon_buf :
309 (canon_buf = vstring_alloc(20)), "{%s}", name));
310 if (table == 0)
311 table = htable_create(1);
312 if (htable_find(table, name) != 0) {
313 msg_warn("ignoring multiple default macro entries for %s in \"%s\"",
314 name, macro_defaults);
315 } else {
316 (void) htable_enter(table, name, mystrdup(value));
317 if (msg_verbose)
318 msg_info("%s: add name=%s default=%s", myname, name, value);
319 }
320 }
321 myfree(saved_defaults);
322 if (canon_buf)
323 vstring_free(canon_buf);
324 return (table);
325}
326
327/* milter_macro_lookup - look up macros */
328
329static ARGV *milter_macro_lookup(MILTERS *milters, const char *macro_names)
330{
331 const char *myname = "milter_macro_lookup";
332 char *saved_names = mystrdup(macro_names);
333 char *cp = saved_names;
334 ARGV *argv = argv_alloc(10);
335 VSTRING *canon_buf = vstring_alloc(20);
336 const char *value;
337 const char *name;
338
339 while ((name = mystrtok(&cp, CHARS_COMMA_SP)) != 0) {
340 if (msg_verbose)
341 msg_info("%s: \"%s\"", myname, name);
342 if (*name != '{') /* } */
343 name = STR(vstring_sprintf(canon_buf, "{%s}", name));
344 if ((value = milters->mac_lookup(name, milters->mac_context)) != 0) {
345 if (msg_verbose)
346 msg_info("%s: result \"%s\"", myname, value);
347 argv_add(argv, name, value, (char *) 0);
348 } else if (milters->macro_defaults != 0
349 && (value = htable_find(milters->macro_defaults, name)) != 0) {
350 if (msg_verbose)
351 msg_info("%s: using default \"%s\"", myname, value);
352 argv_add(argv, name, value, (char *) 0);
353 }
354 }
355 myfree(saved_names);
356 vstring_free(canon_buf);
357 return (argv);
358}

396/* milter_conn_event - report connect event */
397
398const char *milter_conn_event(MILTERS *milters,
399 const char *client_name,
400 const char *client_addr,
401 const char *client_port,
402 unsigned addr_family)
403{
404 const char *resp;
405 MILTER *m;
406 ARGV *global_macros = 0;
407 ARGV *any_macros;
408
409#define MILTER_MACRO_EVAL(global_macros, m, milters, member) \
410 ((m->macros && m->macros->member[0]) ? \
411 milter_macro_lookup(milters, m->macros->member) : \
412 global_macros ? global_macros : \
413 (global_macros = \
414 milter_macro_lookup(milters, milters->macros->member)))
415
416 if (msg_verbose)
417 msg_info("report connect to all milters");
418 for (resp = 0, m = milters->milter_list; resp == 0 && m != 0; m = m->next) {
419 any_macros = MILTER_MACRO_EVAL(global_macros, m, milters, conn_macros);
420 resp = m->conn_event(m, client_name, client_addr, client_port,
421 addr_family, any_macros);
422 if (any_macros != global_macros)
423 argv_free(any_macros);
424 }
425 if (global_macros)
426 argv_free(global_macros);
427 return (resp);
428}

475/* milter_rcpt_event - report rcpt to event */
476
477const char *milter_rcpt_event(MILTERS *milters, int flags, const char **argv)
478{
479 const char *resp;
480 MILTER *m;
481 ARGV *global_macros = 0;
482 ARGV *any_macros;
483
484 if (msg_verbose)
485 msg_info("report recipient to all milters (flags=0x%x)", flags);
486 for (resp = 0, m = milters->milter_list; resp == 0 && m != 0; m = m->next) {
487 if ((flags & MILTER_FLAG_WANT_RCPT_REJ) == 0
488 || (m->flags & MILTER_FLAG_WANT_RCPT_REJ) != 0) {
489 any_macros =
490 MILTER_MACRO_EVAL(global_macros, m, milters, rcpt_macros);
491 resp = m->rcpt_event(m, argv, any_macros);
492 if (any_macros != global_macros)
493 argv_free(any_macros);
494 }
495 }
496 if (global_macros)
497 argv_free(global_macros);
498 return (resp);
499}

559/* milter_message - inspect message content */
560
561const char *milter_message(MILTERS *milters, VSTREAM *fp, off_t data_offset,
562 ARGV *auto_hdrs)
563{
564 const char *resp;
565 MILTER *m;
566 ARGV *global_eoh_macros = 0;
567 ARGV *global_eod_macros = 0;
568 ARGV *any_eoh_macros;
569 ARGV *any_eod_macros;
570
571 if (msg_verbose)
572 msg_info("inspect content by all milters");
573 for (resp = 0, m = milters->milter_list; resp == 0 && m != 0; m = m->next) {
574 any_eoh_macros = MILTER_MACRO_EVAL(global_eoh_macros, m, milters, eoh_macros);
575 any_eod_macros = MILTER_MACRO_EVAL(global_eod_macros, m, milters, eod_macros);
576 resp = m->message(m, fp, data_offset, any_eoh_macros, any_eod_macros,
577 auto_hdrs);
578 if (any_eoh_macros != global_eoh_macros)
579 argv_free(any_eoh_macros);
580 if (any_eod_macros != global_eod_macros)
581 argv_free(any_eod_macros);
582 }
583 if (global_eoh_macros)
584 argv_free(global_eoh_macros);
585 if (global_eod_macros)
586 argv_free(global_eod_macros);
587 return (resp);
588}

590/* milter_abort - cancel message receiving state, all milters */
591
592void milter_abort(MILTERS *milters)
593{
594 MILTER *m;
595
596 if (msg_verbose)
597 msg_info("abort all milters");
598 for (m = milters->milter_list; m != 0; m = m->next)
599 m->abort(m);
600}

602/* milter_disc_event - report client disconnect event to all milters */
603
604void milter_disc_event(MILTERS *milters)
605{
606 MILTER *m;
607
608 if (msg_verbose)
609 msg_info("disconnect event to all milters");
610 for (m = milters->milter_list; m != 0; m = m->next)
611 m->disc_event(m);
612}

614 /*
615 * Table-driven parsing of main.cf parameter overrides for specific Milters.
616 * We derive the override names from the corresponding main.cf parameter
617 * names by skipping the redundant "milter_" prefix.
618 */
619static ATTR_OVER_TIME time_table[] = {
620 7 + VAR_MILT_CONN_TIME, DEF_MILT_CONN_TIME, 0, 1, 0,
621 7 + VAR_MILT_CMD_TIME, DEF_MILT_CMD_TIME, 0, 1, 0,
622 7 + VAR_MILT_MSG_TIME, DEF_MILT_MSG_TIME, 0, 1, 0,
623 0,
624};
625static ATTR_OVER_STR str_table[] = {
626 7 + VAR_MILT_PROTOCOL, 0, 1, 0,
627 7 + VAR_MILT_DEF_ACTION, 0, 1, 0,
628 0,
629};
630
631#define link_override_table_to_variable(table, var) \
632 do { table[var##_offset].target = &var; } while (0)
633
634#define my_conn_timeout_offset 0
635#define my_cmd_timeout_offset 1
636#define my_msg_timeout_offset 2
637
638#define my_protocol_offset 0
639#define my_def_action_offset 1

641/* milter_new - create milter list */
642
643MILTERS *milter_new(const char *names,
644 int conn_timeout,
645 int cmd_timeout,
646 int msg_timeout,
647 const char *protocol,
648 const char *def_action,
649 MILTER_MACROS *macros,
650 HTABLE *macro_defaults)
651{
652 MILTERS *milters;
653 MILTER *head = 0;
654 MILTER *tail = 0;
655 char *name;
656 MILTER *milter;
657 const char *sep = CHARS_COMMA_SP;
658 const char *parens = CHARS_BRACE;
659 int my_conn_timeout;
660 int my_cmd_timeout;
661 int my_msg_timeout;
662 const char *my_protocol;
663 const char *my_def_action;
664
665 /*
666 * Initialize.
667 */
668 link_override_table_to_variable(time_table, my_conn_timeout);
669 link_override_table_to_variable(time_table, my_cmd_timeout);
670 link_override_table_to_variable(time_table, my_msg_timeout);
671 link_override_table_to_variable(str_table, my_protocol);
672 link_override_table_to_variable(str_table, my_def_action);
673
674 /*
675 * Parse the milter list.
676 */
677 milters = (MILTERS *) mymalloc(sizeof(*milters));
678 if (names != 0 && *names != 0) {
679 char *saved_names = mystrdup(names);
680 char *cp = saved_names;
681 char *op;
682 char *err;
683
684 /*
685 * Instantiate Milters, allowing for per-Milter overrides.
686 */
687 while ((name = mystrtokq(&cp, sep, parens)) != 0) {
688 my_conn_timeout = conn_timeout;
689 my_cmd_timeout = cmd_timeout;
690 my_msg_timeout = msg_timeout;
691 my_protocol = protocol;
692 my_def_action = def_action;
693 if (name[0] == parens[0]) {
694 op = name;
695 if ((err = extpar(&op, parens, EXTPAR_FLAG_NONE)) != 0)
696 msg_fatal("milter service syntax error: %s", err);
697 if ((name = mystrtok(&op, sep)) == 0)
698 msg_fatal("empty milter definition: \"%s\"", names);
699 attr_override(op, sep, parens,
700 CA_ATTR_OVER_STR_TABLE(str_table),
701 CA_ATTR_OVER_TIME_TABLE(time_table),
702 CA_ATTR_OVER_END);
703 }
704 milter = milter8_create(name, my_conn_timeout, my_cmd_timeout,
705 my_msg_timeout, my_protocol,
706 my_def_action, milters);
707 if (head == 0) {
708 head = milter;
709 } else {
710 tail->next = milter;
711 }
712 tail = milter;
713 }
714 myfree(saved_names);
715 }
716 milters->milter_list = head;
717 milters->mac_lookup = 0;
718 milters->mac_context = 0;
719 milters->macros = macros;
720 milters->macro_defaults = macro_defaults;
721 milters->add_header = 0;
722 milters->upd_header = milters->ins_header = 0;
723 milters->del_header = 0;
724 milters->add_rcpt = milters->del_rcpt = 0;
725 milters->repl_body = 0;
726 milters->chg_context = 0;
727 return (milters);
728}
729
730/* milter_free - destroy all milters */
731
732void milter_free(MILTERS *milters)
733{
734 MILTER *m;
735 MILTER *next;
736
737 if (msg_verbose)
738 msg_info("free all milters");
739 for (m = milters->milter_list; m != 0; m = next)
740 next = m->next, m->free(m);
741 if (milters->macros)
742 milter_macros_free(milters->macros);
743 if (milters->macro_defaults)
744 htable_free(milters->macro_defaults, myfree);
745 myfree((void *) milters);
746}
747
748/* milter_dummy - send empty milter list */
749
750int milter_dummy(MILTERS *milters, VSTREAM *stream)
751{
752 MILTERS dummy = *milters;
753
754 dummy.milter_list = 0;
755 return (milter_send(&dummy, stream));
756}
757
758/* milter_send - send Milter instances over stream */
759
760int milter_send(MILTERS *milters, VSTREAM *stream)
761{
762 MILTER *m;
763 int status = 0;
764 int count = 0;
765
766 /*
767 * XXX Optimization: send only the filters that are actually used in the
768 * remote process. No point sending a filter that looks at HELO commands
769 * to a cleanup server. For now we skip only the filters that are known
770 * to be disabled (either in global error state or in global accept
771 * state).
772 *
773 * XXX We must send *some* information, even when there are no active
774 * filters, otherwise the cleanup server would try to apply its own
775 * non_smtpd_milters settings.
776 */
777 if (milters != 0)
778 for (m = milters->milter_list; m != 0; m = m->next)
779 if (m->active(m))
780 count++;
781 (void) rec_fprintf(stream, REC_TYPE_MILT_COUNT, "%d", count);
782
783 if (msg_verbose)
784 msg_info("send %d milters", count);
785
786 /*
787 * XXX Optimization: don't send or receive further information when there
788 * aren't any active filters.
789 */
790 if (count <= 0)
791 return (0);
792
793 /*
794 * Send the filter macro name lists.
795 */
796 (void) attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_MORE,
797 SEND_ATTR_FUNC(milter_macros_print,
798 (void *) milters->macros),
799 ATTR_TYPE_END);
800
801 /*
802 * Send the filter macro defaults.
803 */
804 count = milters->macro_defaults ? milters->macro_defaults->used : 0;
805 (void) attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_MORE,
806 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_SIZE, count),
807 ATTR_TYPE_END);
808 if (count > 0)
809 (void) attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_MORE,
810 SEND_ATTR_HASH(milters->macro_defaults),
811 ATTR_TYPE_END);
812
813 /*
814 * Send the filter instances.
815 */
816 for (m = milters->milter_list; m != 0; m = m->next)
817 if (m->active(m) && (status = m->send(m, stream)) != 0)
818 break;
819
820 /*
821 * Over to you.
822 */
823 if (status != 0
824 || attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT,
825 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, &status),
826 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 1
827 || status != 0) {
828 msg_warn("cannot send milters to service %s", VSTREAM_PATH(stream));
829 return (-1);
830 }
831 return (0);
832}
833
834/* milter_receive - receive milters from stream */
835
836MILTERS *milter_receive(VSTREAM *stream, int count)
837{
838 MILTERS *milters;
839 MILTER *head = 0;
840 MILTER *tail = 0;
841 MILTER *milter = 0;
842 int macro_default_count;
843
844 if (msg_verbose)
845 msg_info("receive %d milters", count);
846
847 /*
848 * XXX We must instantiate a MILTERS structure even when the sender has
849 * no active filters, otherwise the cleanup server would try to use its
850 * own non_smtpd_milters settings.
851 */
852#define NO_MILTERS ((char *) 0)
853#define NO_TIMEOUTS 0, 0, 0
854#define NO_PROTOCOL ((char *) 0)
855#define NO_ACTION ((char *) 0)
856#define NO_MACROS ((MILTER_MACROS *) 0)
857#define NO_MACRO_DEFLTS ((HTABLE *) 0)
858
859 milters = milter_new(NO_MILTERS, NO_TIMEOUTS, NO_PROTOCOL, NO_ACTION,
860 NO_MACROS, NO_MACRO_DEFLTS);
861
862 /*
863 * XXX Optimization: don't send or receive further information when there
864 * aren't any active filters.
865 */
866 if (count <= 0)
867 return (milters);
868
869 /*
870 * Receive the global macro name lists.
871 */
872 milters->macros = milter_macros_alloc(MILTER_MACROS_ALLOC_ZERO);
873 if (attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT | ATTR_FLAG_MORE,
874 RECV_ATTR_FUNC(milter_macros_scan,
875 (void *) milters->macros),
876 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 1) {
877 milter_free(milters);
878 return (0);
879 }
880
881 /*
882 * Receive the filter macro defaults.
883 */
884 if (attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT | ATTR_FLAG_MORE,
885 RECV_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_SIZE, &macro_default_count),
886 ATTR_TYPE_END) != 1
887 || (macro_default_count > 0
888 && attr_scan(stream, ATTR_FLAG_STRICT | ATTR_FLAG_MORE,
889 RECV_ATTR_HASH(milters->macro_defaults
890 = htable_create(1)),
891 ATTR_TYPE_END) != macro_default_count)) {
892 milter_free(milters);
893 return (0);
894 }
895
896 /*
897 * Receive the filters.
898 */
899 for (; count > 0; count--) {
900 if ((milter = milter8_receive(stream, milters)) == 0) {
901 msg_warn("cannot receive milters via service %s socket",
902 VSTREAM_PATH(stream));
903 milter_free(milters);
904 return (0);
905 }
906 if (head == 0) {
907 /* Coverity: milter_free() depends on milters->milter_list. */
908 milters->milter_list = head = milter;
909 } else {
910 tail->next = milter;
911 }
912 tail = milter;
913 }
914
915 /*
916 * Over to you.
917 */
918 (void) attr_print(stream, ATTR_FLAG_NONE,
919 SEND_ATTR_INT(MAIL_ATTR_STATUS, 0),
920 ATTR_TYPE_END);
921 return (milters);
922}

924#ifdef TEST
925
926 /*
927 * Proof-of-concept test program. This can be used interactively, but is
928 * typically used for automated regression tests from a script.
929 */
930
931/* System library. */
932
933#include <sys/socket.h>
934#include <stdlib.h>
935#include <string.h>
936
937/* Utility library. */
938
939#include "msg_vstream.h"
940#include "vstring_vstream.h"
941
942/* Global library. */
943
944#include <mail_params.h>
945
946int var_milt_conn_time = 10;
947int var_milt_cmd_time = 10;
948int var_milt_msg_time = 100;
949char *var_milt_protocol = DEF_MILT_PROTOCOL;
950char *var_milt_def_action = DEF_MILT_DEF_ACTION;
951
952static void usage(void)
953{
954 vstream_fprintf(VSTREAM_ERR, "usage: \n"
955 " create names... create and connect\n"
956#if 0
957 " conn_macros names... define connect macros\n"
958 " helo_macros names... define helo command macros\n"
959 " mail_macros names... define mail command macros\n"
960 " rcpt_macros names... define rcpt command macros\n"
961 " data_macros names... define data command macros\n"
962 " unk_macros names... unknown command macros\n"
963 " message_macros names... define message macros\n"
964#endif
965 " free disconnect and destroy\n"
966 " connect name addr port family\n"
967 " helo hostname\n"
968 " ehlo hostname\n"
969 " mail from sender...\n"
970 " rcpt to recipient...\n"
971 " data\n"
972 " disconnect\n"
973 " unknown command\n");
974 vstream_fflush(VSTREAM_ERR);
975}
976
977int main(int argc, char **argv)
978{
979 MILTERS *milters = 0;
980 char *conn_macros, *helo_macros, *mail_macros, *rcpt_macros;
981 char *data_macros, *eoh_macros, *eod_macros, *unk_macros;
982 char *macro_deflts;
983 VSTRING *inbuf = vstring_alloc(100);
984 char *bufp;
985 char *cmd;
986 int ch;
987 int istty = isatty(vstream_fileno(VSTREAM_IN));
988
989 conn_macros = helo_macros = mail_macros = rcpt_macros = data_macros
990 = eoh_macros = eod_macros = unk_macros = macro_deflts = "";
991
992 msg_vstream_init(argv[0], VSTREAM_ERR);
993 while ((ch = GETOPT(argc, argv, "V:v")) > 0) {
994 switch (ch) {
995 default:
996 msg_fatal("usage: %s [-a action] [-p protocol] [-v]", argv[0]);
997 case 'a':
998 var_milt_def_action = optarg;
999 break;
1000 case 'p':
1001 var_milt_protocol = optarg;
1002 break;
1003 case 'v':
1004 msg_verbose++;
1005 break;
1006 }
1007 }
1008 optind = OPTIND;
1009
1010 for (;;) {
1011 const char *resp = 0;
1012 ARGV *argv;
1013 char **args;
1014
1015 if (istty) {
1016 vstream_printf("- ");
1017 vstream_fflush(VSTREAM_OUT);
1018 }
1019 if (vstring_fgets_nonl(inbuf, VSTREAM_IN) <= 0)
1020 break;
1021 bufp = vstring_str(inbuf);
1022 if (!istty) {
1023 vstream_printf("> %s\n", bufp);
1024 vstream_fflush(VSTREAM_OUT);
1025 }
1026 if (*bufp == '#')
1027 continue;
1028 cmd = mystrtok(&bufp, " ");
1029 if (cmd == 0) {
1030 usage();
1031 continue;
1032 }
1033 argv = argv_split(bufp, " ");
1034 args = argv->argv;
1035 if (strcmp(cmd, "create") == 0 && argv->argc == 1) {
1036 if (milters != 0) {
1037 msg_warn("deleting existing milters");
1038 milter_free(milters);
1039 }
1040 milters = milter_create(args[0], var_milt_conn_time,
1041 var_milt_cmd_time, var_milt_msg_time,
1042 var_milt_protocol, var_milt_def_action,
1043 conn_macros, helo_macros, mail_macros,
1044 rcpt_macros, data_macros, eoh_macros,
1045 eod_macros, unk_macros, macro_deflts);
1046 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "free") == 0 && argv->argc == 0) {
1047 if (milters == 0) {
1048 msg_warn("no milters");
1049 continue;
1050 }
1051 milter_free(milters);
1052 milters = 0;
1053 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "connect") == 0 && argv->argc == 4) {
1054 if (milters == 0) {
1055 msg_warn("no milters");
1056 continue;
1057 }
1058 resp = milter_conn_event(milters, args[0], args[1], args[2],
1059 strcmp(args[3], "AF_INET") == 0 ? AF_INET :
1060 strcmp(args[3], "AF_INET6") == 0 ? AF_INET6 :
1061 strcmp(args[3], "AF_UNIX") == 0 ? AF_UNIX :
1062 AF_UNSPEC);
1063 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "helo") == 0 && argv->argc == 1) {
1064 if (milters == 0) {
1065 msg_warn("no milters");
1066 continue;
1067 }
1068 resp = milter_helo_event(milters, args[0], 0);
1069 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "ehlo") == 0 && argv->argc == 1) {
1070 if (milters == 0) {
1071 msg_warn("no milters");
1072 continue;
1073 }
1074 resp = milter_helo_event(milters, args[0], 1);
1075 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "mail") == 0 && argv->argc > 0) {
1076 if (milters == 0) {
1077 msg_warn("no milters");
1078 continue;
1079 }
1080 resp = milter_mail_event(milters, (const char **) args);
1081 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "rcpt") == 0 && argv->argc > 0) {
1082 if (milters == 0) {
1083 msg_warn("no milters");
1084 continue;
1085 }
1086 resp = milter_rcpt_event(milters, 0, (const char **) args);
1087 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "unknown") == 0 && argv->argc > 0) {
1088 if (milters == 0) {
1089 msg_warn("no milters");
1090 continue;
1091 }
1092 resp = milter_unknown_event(milters, args[0]);
1093 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "data") == 0 && argv->argc == 0) {
1094 if (milters == 0) {
1095 msg_warn("no milters");
1096 continue;
1097 }
1098 resp = milter_data_event(milters);
1099 } else if (strcmp(cmd, "disconnect") == 0 && argv->argc == 0) {
1100 if (milters == 0) {
1101 msg_warn("no milters");
1102 continue;
1103 }
1104 milter_disc_event(milters);
1105 } else {
1106 usage();
1107 }
1108 if (resp != 0)
1109 msg_info("%s", resp);
1110 argv_free(argv);
1111 }
1112 if (milters != 0)
1113 milter_free(milters);
1114 vstring_free(inbuf);
1115 return (0);
1116}
